By 144 Myr, subduction zone EW has decreased its western extent while deformation on Plate B along the boundary between B and C has increased. The period between 108 and 144 Myr includes a shorter time window, between roughly 124-136 Myr, during which Plates A and C undergo rapid changes in the positions and magnitudes of their respective Euler vectors, corresponding to substantial directional change in their motion.Fig. 1
