The direction changes associated with the three plates discussed, and the abruptness of the reorganization event marked by the direction changes, are depicted in Fig. 3. The time series for Plate A shows that from 45 to 125 Myr the plate interior gradually increases velocity, following a steady decrease in the previous 20 Myr. The full 80 Myr period of velocity increase is punctuated by four episodes of clockwise plate direction change, the last of which (at 90 Myr) interrupts two distinct counter-clockwise rotations. From 125 Myr onwards the directional plate velocity changes are steady as is a magnitude increase. In contrast, the velocity at the centre of Plate B remains approximately 5 cm/yr for most of the history examined. For roughly 120 Myr, Plate C’s direction changes slowly while its speed decreases from 6 to 2 cm/yr. However, commencing at approximately 124 Myr its velocity shows a very rapid and dramatic change. The total change in direction during this reorganization event is approximately 90\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
