Fig. S7 shows timeseries of the mean age within the areas comprising each plate. The ages are determined by calculating the surface heat flux over each plate and approximating age using the half-space cooling model while implementing information about the temperature of the mantle at the divergent plate boundaries. Consistent with the time series of plate velocity included in Fig. 3, we find mean plate age increases at times when plate velocities are decreasing. Given that Plate B, and especially Plate C, ages more rapidly during the reorganization event, we conclude that their shared convergent boundary will experience a reduction in subduction flux. Plate A shows slight decrease in age so that subduction flux likely remains somewhat steady between A and C during the reorganization event.Fig. 2
